Definition.WordDefinition: Acne \Ac"ne\, n. [NL., prob. a corruption of Gr. ?] (Med.) A pustular affection of the skin, due to changes in the sebaceous glands. [1913 Webster]
acne n : an inflammatory disease involving the sebaceous glands of the skin; characterized by papules or pustules or comedones
